sec.p:
Cystic metastases were defined as a combination of a large cystic portion (cyst volume) and the remaining solid portion (solid volume). Cystic portion was defined as a discrete fluid-filled component hypointense on T1-weighted imaging surrounded by ring-enhancing wall, and iso to hyperintense on T2-weighted imaging [6]. Large cysts were defined as those with cyst volume ≥ 5 mL [14]. Based on diffusion-weighted imaging (DWI), cyst center was labeled as secretion of tumor exudate (low intensity in DWI), and as liquefactive necrosis (iso to high intensity in DWI). Volumes were calculated using Leksell GammaPlan® (Elekta Instruments) based on gadolinium-enhanced magnetic resonance imaging (Gd-MRI). The original tumor volume (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
